This chartulary of the Priory of St. Andrews appears to have escaped the notice of Dalrymple, Sibbald, Keith, and other antiquaries of the beginning of the last century; and its existence was unknown even to Martine, the local historiari of St. Andrews, and his editor.

Another and altogether different Register of the same house did indeed excite great attention, and, when lost, was the cause of much regret to the Scotch his- torical enquirer.
